 interpretive text. They include: The People: changes in population and settlement partterns; distribution of Native peoples; growth of the labour force. The Environment: geological, topographical, and climatic features; concentration of fish and game. Resource Use: distribution of natural resources; development of indstury; communication and transportation links; location of energy resources; development of recreational lands. The atlas has 115 maps, 74 illustrations, tables and diagrams. Bold colours and explicit keys contribue to the easy, rapid interpretation of data. A Gazetteer and an Historical and Statistical Summary are included to provide a quick reference for the most commonly sought facts and to supplement maps and text.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aSCIENCE / Earth Sciences / Geography.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia eBook-Package Pre-2000z978311141940440uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077485788840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774857888423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774857888/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  a978-3-11-141940-4  University of British Columbia eBook-Package Pre-2000b2000  aGBV-deGruyter-alles